title: Menai Roosters
text:
The Menai Roosters Rugby League Football Club (also known as <a href="Menai%20District">Menai District</a>) is a <a href="rugby%20league">rugby league</a> football club that was formed in 1981 and competes in the <a href="Cronulla-Sutherland%20District%20Rugby%20Football%20League">Cronulla-Sutherland District Rugby Football League</a>. The club is based out of Akuna Oval at <a href="Bangor%2C%20New%20South%20Wales">Bangor</a> where its clubhouse and headquarters are located and usually draws the large majority of its junior players from <a href="Menai%2C%20New%20South%20Wales">Menai</a> and the surrounding suburbs of Bangor, <a href="Illawong%2C%20New%20South%20Wales">Illawong</a>, <a href="Alfords%20Point%2C%20New%20South%20Wales">Alfords Point</a> and <a href="Barden%20Ridge%2C%20New%20South%20Wales">Barden Ridge</a>.
The Menai club currently field teams from Under 6 age groups all the way up to A Grade.
